  print("All data frames have the 'submitter_id' column.")

  print("Some data frames are missing the 'submitter_id' column.")
  print(column_check)

library(ggplot2)

# Plot for Concordance
plot_results_all_table_interaction <- ggplot(results_all_table_interaction, aes(x = test_name, y = concordance, fill = "Interaction")) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
  geom_bar(data = results_all_table_non_interaction, aes(x = test_name, y = concordance, fill = "Non-Interaction"),
           stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(
    title = "Comparison of Concordance",
    x = "Test Name",
    y = "Concordance"
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Interaction" = "blue", "Non-Interaction" = "red")) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

show(plot_results_all_table_interaction)

# Plot for Likelihood Ratio DF
ggplot(results_all_table_interaction, aes(x = test_name, y = likelihood_ratio_df, fill = "Interaction")) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
  geom_bar(data = results_all_table_non_interaction, aes(x = test_name, y = likelihood_ratio_df, fill = "Non-Interaction"),
           stat = "identity", position = "dodge", alpha = 0.7) +
  labs(
    title = "Comparison of Likelihood Ratio DF",
    x = "Test Name",
    y = "Likelihood Ratio DF"
  ) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Interaction" = "blue", "Non-Interaction" = "red")) +
